Quadruped ROS2 Navigation - Notices

This workspace contains the navigation, mapping, localization, obstacle
avoidance, sensor-driver, and motion-interface portions of a quadruped robot
project.

First-party / project packages:
- src/quadruped_navigation_bringup: Apache-2.0
- src/gicp_localization: Apache-2.0
- src/lidar_scan_bridge: Apache-2.0
- src/pcd2pgm: Apache-2.0
- src/my_nav: MIT
- src/agibot_motion_service: Apache-2.0

Third-party packages kept in active src:
- src/FAST_LIO: GPL-2.0-only, see src/FAST_LIO/LICENSE.
- src/livox_ros_driver2: MIT/Livox license text, see src/livox_ros_driver2/LICENSE.txt.
- src/livox_ros_driver2/3rdparty/rapidjson: see its bundled license.txt.
- src/agibot_motion_service/third_party/zsibot_sdk-0.2.6: BSD-3-Clause, see its LICENSE.

Optional packages under unused_packages:
- LIO-SAM: BSD-3-Clause, optional graph-SLAM package, see unused_packages/LIO-SAM/LICENSE.
- livox_repub: Apache-2.0, optional Livox CustomMsg to PointCloud2 bridge.
- rslidar_msg, rsLiDAR_sdk, rs_driver: RoboSense LiDAR support, BSD-3-Clause/upstream licenses.
- serial, yesense_interface, yesense_std_ros2: external serial/YESENSE IMU support, Apache/upstream licenses.
- legacy_agibot_driver: Apache-2.0 reference package for the old AgiBot bridge path.

Large sample and map assets are intentionally kept in this repository for now,
including existing PCD maps, PGM maps, and upstream package media.
Consider Git LFS later if repository size becomes a problem.
